Pucker was a band active in Davis from 19911994.  Members included Howard Myint (Vocals and Guitar), Amr Toppozada (Vocals and Bass), and Chad McDonald (Vocals and Guitar) as well as multiple drummers, most notably Stewart Eastham.  They played shows at Mansion Cellars, The G Street Pub, Cheezers Pizza, multiple parties, and Live in Studio A on KDVS.

The original name of the band was Barking Spider but was changed when it was determined that another band from Santa Cruz had the same name.  Members of the band went on to become part of multiple other groups:
Baltimore, Kevins Mom, The Orange Wedgies, Illmatik Vibes, Lunchbox, The Long Pigs, Single, Minibike, Day of the Outlaw, etc.
